         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1/6/78 ¶ It was very pleasing to me, dear Dr Beccari, to get your kind letter from Singapore, dated 19. April. ¶  Let me hope, that you will find your position in Florence amidst your riches &amp; treasur...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.06.01a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/6/78</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">It was very pleasing to me, dear Dr Beccari, to get your kind letter from Singapore, dated 19. April.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> Let me hope, that you will find your position in Florence amidst your riches &amp; treasures, congenial to your tastes! What a path of glory have you before you! As regards Signor D'Albertis's plants,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Luigi Maria d'Albertis.</p>
               </note> I shall of course be grateful for any, which you can spare me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I met D'Albertis here for two days, which was a source of great pleasure to me. He left a few living plants, which will likely come under my cognizance, when in flower.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Australia is almost exhausted, so far as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg> plants are concerned. Hence I must rely on New Guinea or some other part of the globe for novelties.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is quite likely, that I mistook a <name key="Platea">Platea</name> for a <name key="Lasianthera">Lasianthera</name> or <name key="Gomphandra">Gomphandra</name>, as I had not the benefit of using your excellent memoir on <name key="Olacineae">Olacineae</name>, when I worked out the only Australian species as yet known. I will send you a specimen.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M did not publish a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Platea">Platea</name>
                     </seg>. In B76.12.03, p. 53, he identified a specimen collected by Luigi Maria D'Albertis at the Fly River in Papua as Miquel's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Lasianthera">Lasianthera</name> litoralis</seg>, but Beccari (1877-90), vol. 1, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 257 synonymized it as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Platea">Platea</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">papuana</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray remember me kindly to the friendly Capt. D'Albertis,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Luigi Maria d'Albertis was travelling from Sydney to London and visited M during the period the SS </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Garonne</seg>
                     <seg style=""> was in Melbourne— from 7 May, until it 'cleared out' on 10 May (Argus, 8 May 1878, p. 4; 11 May 1878, p. 6).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and give also my compliments to Dr Scheffer, from whom I have not heard for a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very</hi>
               </seg> long time,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. Scheffer to M, .25 October 1877.</p>
               </note> though I believe, that he is in frequent communication with the Nurseryman at the bot. Garden.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Guilfoyle.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I like very much to obtain Bamboo-<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">seeds </hi>
               </seg>of any kind in quantity fit for germination, and could send <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> seeds in exchange.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am making grand efforts to restore my Directorship and to place the Gardener on the parks &amp; Reserves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regardful remembrance, dear Dr Beccari, </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">your obliged</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva, Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
